{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-03-26-how-to-add-background-image-in-react-using-css/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add background image in react using css, you can use    in . It will add background image in react using css. Today, I‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add background image in react using css, you can use   <code class=\"language-text\">background-image: url('nature.jpg');</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">.background-image</code>. It will add background image in react using css.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add background image in react using css.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component..</h2>\n<p>you can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;React.Fragment></code> and add background image in react using css.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"background-image\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Content of your component */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Define the add background image in react using css example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">React</code>. and use <code class=\"language-text\">background-image: url('nature.jpg');` in `.background-image</code> to add background image in react using css.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Import the CSS file</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">BackgroundImage</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"background-image\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Content of your component */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> BackgroundImage<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\">\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* App.css */</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.background-image</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background-image</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token url\"><span class=\"token function\">url</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string url\">'nature.jpg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> cover<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background-position</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100vh<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">  background-image: url('nature.jpg');</code> component and add background image in react using css.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/aca34/add-background-image-using-css.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.632911392405056%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRn4AAABXRUJQVlA4IHIAAAAwBACdASoUAAoAPtFWo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJZACdMoR3ACm/3DElYNBZDQAA/eO7rYJOnNpv7y7Dq7vkWHyGQa1uCVAf1RWgFeTQAcZSg2Dk91X5Yslfn+RW4g52QG2+ZjLfRH8EacAJO9+UxafC/DxrQAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, background, image, using, css\"\n        title=\"React, add, background, image, using, css\"\n        src=\"/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/8aab1/add-background-image-using-css.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/81b7c/add-background-image-using-css.webp 158w,\n/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/6ea66/add-background-image-using-css.webp 315w,\n/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/8aab1/add-background-image-using-css.webp 630w,\n/static/9c8c8f02d54125dc2afa77f22e9e8e88/a70f5/add-background-image-using-css.webp 945w,\n